    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Historical Information 
</head>
      <p>Pittsylvania County was named in honor of William Pitt, earl of Chatham, a great English statesman.  It was formed from Halifax County in 1766.
</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>Pittsylvania County (Va.) Land Records, 1796-1812, 1883, consist of a List of Conveyances and a Processioners' Book.
</p>
